Package: visStatistics
Type: Package
Title: Visualization of the most powerful statistical hypothesis test between two groups of data.
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Schilling", "Sabine", email = "sabineschilling@gmx.ch", role = c("cre","aut")),
    person("Kauf", "Peter", email = "peter.kauf@zhaw.ch", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Sabine Schilling<sabineschilling@gmx.ch>
Description: Visualization of the statistical hypothesis test between two groups of data.
    The function vistat visualizes the statistical hypothesis testing between two group
    of data, where varsample is the dependent variable (or response) and varfactor is the independent variable(feature). 
    The statistical hypothesis test including corresponding post-hoc analysis with the highest statistical power and fulfilling
    the assumptions of   the corresponding test is performed and visualized. 
    A graph displaying the raw data accordingly to the chosen test as well as the test statistics is generated and returned.
    Implemented tests: lm, t.test, wilcox.test, aov, kruskal.test, fisher.test,chisqu.test.
Imports: Cairo, multcompView,vcd,stats, grDevices, graphics, utils
